{"headline": "What Song Makes You Nostalgic?", "body": "\nPerhaps it\u2019s the song that was playing the evening he proposed. Or the sound of an Israeli folk tune that in an instant returns you to the summer camp of your childhood. Music has the power to evoke poignant memories from our past, making us feel sentimental for a time long gone.         \n\nIn a coming issue of Science Times, John Tierney will explore the science behind nostalgia. Ahead of his article, we want to hear from you.         \n\nIn the comments below, tell us the name of a song (along with the band or singer who performed it) that sets off a flight of nostalgia for you. Then describe the related event and how it makes you feel. Include your name, location and age. We will publish a selection of the responses and song tracks.        ", "url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2013/06/24/science/what-song-makes-you-nostalgic.html", "date": "2013-06-24", "description": "Music has the power to evoke poignant memories, making us feel sentimental for a time long gone."}